    "description": "How Do You Change Your Name on Roblox? A Complete Guide to Updating Your Username\n\n<strong>how do you change your name on roblox<\/strong> is a question many players ask once they’ve spent some time in the game and want to refresh their identity or just try something new. Roblox is a massively popular online platform where millions create, play, and share games, and your username is often your first impression. Whether you chose a name in haste, want to rebrand yourself, or just feel like a change, knowing how to update your Roblox name is key to staying connected with friends and the community.\n\nChanging your Roblox username isn’t complicated, but there are some important details and limitations you should be aware of. In this article, we’ll walk you through the entire process step-by-step, explain the costs involved, and share some practical tips to make the most of your new identity on Roblox.\n\n<h2>Understanding Roblox Usernames vs. Display Names<\/h2>\n\nBefore diving into the actual process of changing your name, it’s helpful to understand the difference between a Roblox username and a display name. These two terms often get confused but serve different purposes.\n\n<h3>Username: Your Unique Identifier<\/h3>\n\nYour Roblox username is a unique identifier that you use to log in and that other players use to find you. It’s permanent unless you decide to change it manually, and no two players can have the same username. When you first create your Roblox account, you pick this username, and it sticks with you unless updated.\n\n<h3>Display Name: A Flexible Alias<\/h3>\n\nRoblox introduced the display name feature to give users more freedom in how their name appears to others. Unlike usernames, display names can be changed for free once every seven days and don’t have to be unique. For example, many players might have the display name “GamerPro,” but their usernames will always be distinct.\n\nThis means if you want a quick, cost-free way to change how your name appears in games and chats, updating your display name might be the better option. But if you want to change your actual login username, which shows up on your profile URL and is unique, you’ll need to go through a different process.\n\n<h2>How Do You Change Your Name on Roblox? Step-by-Step Guide<\/h2>\n\nNow that you know the difference between username and display name, here’s how you can change each one. Keep in mind, changing your username comes with a fee, while the display name change is free but limited to once per week.\n\n<h3>Changing Your Roblox Username<\/h3>\n\n1. **Log in to your Roblox account** on the official Roblox website using your current username and password.\n2. Click on the **gear icon** at the top-right corner to open the settings menu.\n3. Select **Settings** from the dropdown.\n4. Under the **Account Info** tab, locate the **Username** section.\n5. Click the **Edit** button next to your username.\n6. Enter your desired new username. Roblox will automatically check if it’s available.\n7. If the username is available and fits Roblox’s naming rules, you’ll be prompted to pay a fee of **1,000 Robux** (Roblox’s in-game currency).\n8. Confirm the transaction to finalize the change.\n\n**Important:** Roblox charges 1,000 Robux each time you change your username, so make sure you pick a name you really want before committing.\n\n<h3>Changing Your Roblox Display Name<\/h3>\n\n1. Log in to your Roblox account.\n2. Go to the **Settings** page by clicking the gear icon.\n3. Under the **Account Info** tab, find the **Display Name** field.\n4. Click the **Edit** button next to it.\n5. Type your desired display name.\n6. Click **Save**.\n\nYour new display name will appear across Roblox games and chats immediately. Remember, you can only change your display name once every seven days, but it’s free.\n\n<h2>Tips for Choosing a New Roblox Username<\/h2>\n\nChanging your username on Roblox is a big deal since it represents your online identity. Here are some tips to help you pick a great new name and avoid frustrations:\n\n<ul>\n  <li><strong>Check availability beforehand:<\/strong> Popular or simple names often get taken quickly. Use Roblox’s username checker to see if your desired name is free.<\/li>\n  <li><strong>Follow Roblox’s username guidelines:<\/strong> Usernames must be 3-20 characters, can include letters, numbers, and underscores, but no spaces or special characters.<\/li>\n  <li><strong>Keep it appropriate:<\/strong> Roblox has strict rules about names. Avoid offensive or inappropriate words to prevent your username from being rejected or flagged.<\/li>\n  <li><strong>Consider longevity:<\/strong> Since changing your username costs Robux, try to choose a name you’ll be happy with for a long time.<\/li>\n  <li><strong>Use a mix of letters and numbers:<\/strong> If your ideal name is taken, adding numbers or creative spelling might help.<\/li>\n<\/ul>\n\n<h2>What Happens After You Change Your Roblox Username?<\/h2>\n\nOnce you successfully change your username, several things happen:\n\n- Your new username will be displayed on your profile and in-game.\n- Your old username becomes available for others to claim (so be mindful that someone else might take your previous name).\n- Your friends list and messages stay intact; you won’t lose any of your social connections.\n- Your profile URL will update to reflect your new username, which can affect how you share your profile with others.\n\nIt’s a good idea to notify your friends or followers about your new username to avoid confusion, especially if you’re part of active Roblox communities or groups.\n\n<h2>How to Get Robux for Changing Your Username<\/h2>\n\nSince changing your Roblox username requires 1,000 Robux, you might wonder how to acquire this currency if you don’t have enough.\n\n<h3>Ways to Earn Robux<\/h3>\n\n<ul>\n  <li><strong>Purchase Robux:<\/strong> The simplest method is to buy Robux directly from Roblox via credit card