splay Name on Roblox<\/h2>\n\nFor those seeking a cost-free alternative, here’s how to change your display name:\n\n<ol>\n  <li>Log into your Roblox account.<\/li>\n  <li>Go to the “Settings” menu by clicking the gear icon.<\/li>\n  <li>Under “Account Info,” locate the “Display Name” field.<\/li>\n  <li>Type your desired display name and ensure it complies with Roblox rules.<\/li>\n  <li>Click “Save” to apply the new display name.<\/li>\n  <li>Note that display names can be changed once every seven days.<\/li>\n<\/ol>\n\nThis option enables users to refresh their public identity without financial cost or login disruptions.\n\n<h2>Why Does Roblox Charge for Username Changes?<\/h2>\n\nCharging for username changes serves multiple purposes:\n\n<ul>\n  <li><strong>Reducing Abuse:<\/strong> A financial barrier helps prevent users from frequently changing usernames to evade bans or harass others.<\/li>\n  <li><strong>Maintaining Community Stability:<\/strong> Consistency in usernames helps players recognize each other, fostering a stable community environment.<\/li>\n  <li><strong>Generating Revenue:<\/strong> As a free-to-play platform, Roblox relies on Robux sales for revenue, and username changes contribute to this ecosystem.<\/li>\n<\/ul>\n\nWhile this approach may seem restrictive, it balances user freedom with platform integrity.\n\n<h2>Additional Tips for Managing Your Roblox Identity<\/h2>\n\nChanging your username or display name is only one part of managing your Roblox identity. Consider these recommendations:\n\n<ul>\n  <li><strong>Keep Your Account Secure:<\/strong> Enable two-step verification to protect your account from unauthorized changes.<\/li>\n  <li><strong>Inform Your Friends:<\/strong> Notify your friends and communities when you change your username to avoid confusion.<\/li>\n  <li><strong>Choose a Timeless Name:<\/strong> Since username changes are costly, select a name that will remain relevant over time.<\/li>\n  <li><strong>Use Display Names for